div.p:
Two Months were ſpent in this Work;
the Ship was call'd the St. Catherine, of
four hundred Tun, carrying forty Guns;
'twas built at Fleſſingue, and deſign'd for
a Cruiſer; Captain Monſegue commanded
it by orders of the Company.

But his guilt was not long a puniſhing;
for returning home with his Goods,
he meets a chief Lord, who ſtript him
of all he had, made him a Slave, and
ſold him to the Factory.



The Teeth of their Iron-headed Arrow
produces another miſerable effect;
for they can't be drawn back,
without making the Wound more dangerous
than before.
